#!/usr/bin/env bash #forked from OneUpdater by Vitor Galvao https://github.com/vitorgalvao/alfred-workflows/blob/master/OneUpdater/README.md
readonly remote_info_plist='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erikopinaldo/alfred-zendesk-shortcuts/main/info.plist' readonly workflow_url='erikopinaldo/alfred-zendesk-shortcuts' readonly download_type='github_release' readonly frequency_check='4' # readonly auth=$(cat '.assets/vars.txt') readonly home_page='https://app.slack.com/client/E12KS1G65/Qp:F0739LHNY5R'
#FROM HERE ON, CODE SHOULD BE LEFT UNTOUCHED! function abort { echo "${1}" >&2 exit 1 }
#check to see if the URL can be reached function url_exists { curl --silent --location -H 'Accept: application/vnd.github.v3.raw' --output /dev/null --fail --range 0-0 "${1}" }
#notifications. Uses 'Notificator'. function notification { local -r notificator="$(find . -type f -name 'notificator')" if [[ -f "${notificator}" && "$(/usr/bin/file --brief --mime-type "${notificator}")" == 'text/x-shellscript' ]]; then "${notificator}" --message "${1}" --title "ZD Shortcuts for Alfred" --subtitle "${2}" --sound 'Funk' return fi
#use applescript if Notificator fails osascript -e "display notification \"${1}\" with title \"Alfred ${alfred_workflow_name} Updater \" subtitle \"${2}\"" }
# Local sanity checks readonly local_info_plist='info.plist' readonly local_version="$(/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'print version' "${local_info_plist}")"
[[ -n "${local_version}" ]] || abort 'You need to set a workflow version in the configuration sheet.'
# Check for updates if [[ $(find "${local_info_plist}" -mtime +"${frequency_check}"d) ]]; then if ! url_exists "${remote_info_plist}"; then abort "'remote_info_plist' (${remote_info_plist}) appears to not be reachable."; fi # Remote sanity check
#this creates a temp file to compare with the local version. readonly tmp_file="$(mktemp)" curl --location --output "${tmp_file}" "${remote_info_plist}" -H 'Accept: application/vnd.github.v3.raw' readonly remote_version="$(/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'print version' "${tmp_file}")"
#compare the local with remote to see if an update is available. if [[ "${local_version}" == "${remote_version}" ]]; then notification 'You are up to date!' touch "${local_info_plist}" # Reset timer by touching local file exit 0 fi
if [[ "${download_type}" == 'page' ]]; then notification 'Launching update in Slack…' open "${workflow_url}" exit 0 fi
download_url="$([[ "${download_type}" == 'github_release' ]] && curl --silent "https://api.github.com/repos/${workflow_url}/releases/latest" | grep 'browser_download_url' | head -1 | sed -E 's/.*browser_download_url": "(.*)"/\1/' || echo "${workflow_url}")" echo "${download_url}"
if url_exists "${download_url}"; then notification 'Downloading and installing…''Update available v'""${remote_version}"" curl -H 'Accept: application/vnd.github.v3.raw' --location --output "${HOME}/Downloads/${alfred_workflow_name}-${remote_version}.alfredworkflow" "${download_url}" open "${HOME}/Downloads/${alfred_workflow_name}-${remote_version}.alfredworkflow" else #if the update download cannot be reached, open the workflow channel in TS
open "${home_page}" notification "Download in #watch-erik-code-things" 'Update available v'""${remote_version}"" abort "'workflow_url' (${download_url}) appears to not be reachable." fi fi

getIds() "

on alfred_script(q)
set theCount to 0
tell application "System Events"
repeat with i from 1 to 10
if exists (window 1 of process "Sleuth") then exit repeat end if
set theCount to theCount + 1
delay 1
end repeat
end tell
return theCount end alfred_script

latest_log="${logFolder}$(mdls -n kMDItemFSName -n kMDItemDateAdded -raw ${logFolder}*.{zip,txt} | xargs -0 -n2 | sort -rn | head -n1 | cut -d' ' -f4-)"
echo -n $latest_log

==============================
v2.2.1 Update - Oct 5, 2024
==============================
Update HTML class targeting for opening ZD views.
===============
ABOUT
===============
Keyboard shortcuts for Zendesk.
* Ticket assignment actions * Assign to Support * Assign to Self * Assign to Self and set to On Hold * Assign to Self and set to Pending
* Misc ticket actions * NEW! Open most recently downloaded log file in Sleuth * NEW! Copy user/team ID from lefthand ticket sidebar * [PLAY MODE] Next ticket * Toggle formatting menu * Close current ticket tab * Copy requester first name
* ZD view shortcuts * Shortcuts for opening up to 5 views (see instructions below) * Go to a specific view and show notification for total # of tickets updated “today” * Open my profile * [SEARCH RESULTS] Set search date filter to “Past Year” * Refresh all views
===========================
HOW TO ADD VIEW SHORTCUTS
===========================
1. Open your ZD view in browser
2. Get the VIEW ID at the end of the URL
3a. [Alfred 4] In the "Variables" box to the left, double click any value field for the variable "viewX"
3b. [Alfred 5] Import this workflow, click on the [x] icon at the top right of Alfred > Environment Variables > double click any value field for the variable "viewX"
4. Paste VIEW ID
5. Import
=================================
HOW TO SET UP LATEST LOG OPENER
=================================
1. Open Finder
2. In the menubar at the very top of your screen, click View > Show Path Bar (or use Option + Command + P)
3. Open the folder where your logs are normally downloaded to
4. You'll see your log folder icon in the Path Bar at the bottom of the Finder window. Right-click that folder icon and click on 'Copy "FOLDER_NAME" as Pathname'
5a. [Alfred 4] In the "Variables" box to the left, double click the value field for the variable "logFolder"
5b. [Alfred 5] Import this workflow, click on the [x] icon at the top right of Alfred > Environment Variables > double click the value field for the variable "logFolder"
6. Paste the Pathname you previously copied
7. Import
